\begin{document}
}{}\begin{equation*} \mathrm{NCR}_{y}(d) = \frac{\sum _{\lbrace i \in P | p_{\mathrm{Year}}=y \mbox{ and } i_{\mathrm{Disease}}=d\rbrace }\sum _{\lbrace j \in P \rbrace } j \in i_{\mathrm{citations}}}{|\lbrace j \in P | j_{\mathrm{Year}}=y\rbrace j_{\mathrm{citations}}|} \end{equation*}\end{document}

Normalized Paper Rate (NPR)—the ratio between the Number of Papers published on a specific infectious disease d and the total number of papers in the fields of medicine or biology in the year y.
